	abstract = {{\textless}p{\textgreater}The Alaiz experiment (ALEX17) was performed at Alaiz, located in Navarre region (Spain), a site consisting of a mountain range of 1000m above sea level (a.s.l.). To the North, along the prevailing wind direction, measurement equipment are located at a valley 500m lower in altitude bounded by a 750 m asl. hill located 6 km north of Alaiz.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}{\textless}br{\textgreater}{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}The experimental layout aims to provide a high-quality database to explore wind flow phenomena and derive validation datasets of high-resolution mesoscale-to-microscale models with strong coupling between terrain and thermal stratification.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}{\textless}br{\textgreater}{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}This full-scale experiment is a joint effort between research groups of Technical University of Denmark (DTU), Renewable Energy Centre of Spain (CENER) and University of Balearic Islands (UIB).{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}{\textless}br{\textgreater}{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}The dataset collection is divided into the following parts, which can be accessed below and downloaded via OpenDAP:{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}{\textless}br{\textgreater}{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Multi-lidar dataset: 5 x Long-range WindScanner (LRWS) systems{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Surface fluxes dataset: 9 x Surface Layer Stations (SLS){\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• WLS70 dataset: 1 x Windcube 70 (WLS70) lidar profiler{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Alaiz Test Site dataset: 1 x 118m flux-profile meteorological mast (called MP5){\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• SEB and RASS dataset: 1 x Surface Energy Budget Station (SEB) and 1 x WindRASS sodar system{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Navarre meteo stations dataset: 22 x surface climatological stations from Meteo Navarra{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Flux-profile dataset: 4 x 80m met masts equipped with 3D sonic anemometers{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Complementary measurements dataset: 2 x 80m met masts with cup anemometers along with 6x80m temperature and relative humidity profiles.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}• Landscape dataset: Digital Elevation Model (DEM) with 2x2m resolution as well as derived roughness length with 10x10m resolution.{\textless}br{\textgreater}{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
	language = {en},
	urldate = {2020-07-22},
	author = {Santos, Pedro and Mann, Jakob and Vasiljevic, Nikola and Courtney, Michael and Sanz Rodrigo, Javier and Cantero, Elena and Borbón, Fernando and Martínez-Villagrasa, Daniel and Martí, Belén and Cuxart, Joan},
